Phase 3 Execution Checklist

This is the minimum acceptable bar.
If any box fails, you are not actually “in Phase 3 execution readiness.”

Ownership & Accountability

 A single responsible organization is named

 A single accountable individual is named

 Lines of authority are explicit

 Budget authority is confirmed

Scope Lock

 Phase 0 intent unchanged

 Phase 1 boundaries preserved

 Phase 2 assumptions acknowledged (not re-debated)

 Out-of-scope items explicitly listed

Technical Readiness

 Architecture frozen to versioned baseline

 Success criteria defined in measurable form

 Failure kill criteria defined

 Integration assumptions documented

 Known risks listed without hand-waving

Schedule & Money Reality

 Execution timeline exists

 Budget line exists

 Review cadence defined

 Decision gates defined

 “Stop spending” trigger exists

Legal & License Compliance

 Execution rights cleared

 Non-commercial vs commercial boundaries understood

 Attribution / license obligations acknowledged

If you cannot check every box, you are not ready.
If you refuse to check every box, you do not want Phase 3 — you want theater.
